oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Practical Vehicle Management
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Jernigen, L. D.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: I practice about 40 miles south of Manhattan, Kansas. My type of vehicle might be a bit different, but it seems to work in my practice very well. I have just a one man, general practice. You might say it is the old type, mainly ambulatory, mainly beef cattle. I have used a van for a number of years, fitted with a large box with a lot of drawers. I know different veterinarians have different ideas about what they like for ambulatory vehicles.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 1973; 39
